tidylife 0.1.0
  • Reference

    Conflicts between tidylife packages and other packages

    tidylife_conflicts.Rd

    This function lists all the conflicts between packages in the tidylife collection and other packages that you have loaded.

    tidylife_conflicts()

    Value

    A list object of class tidylife_conflicts.

    Details

    Some conflicts are deliberately ignored: intersect, union, setequal, and setdiff from dplyr; and intersect, union, setdiff, and as.difftime from lubridate. These functions make the base equivalents generic, so shouldn't negatively affect any existing code.

    Examples

    tidylife_conflicts()
#> ── Conflicts ───────────────────────────────────────────── tidylife_conflicts ──
#> ✖ dplyr::filter()      masks stats::filter()
#> ✖ tsibble::intersect() masks base::intersect()
#> ✖ dplyr::lag()         masks stats::lag()
#> ✖ tsibble::setdiff()   masks base::setdiff()
#> ✖ tsibble::union()     masks base::union()
